column5: Might as well get this thing started up. What are the water levels like at and around Lac Suel?
Deekon, Try this website. Lac Seul is covered by the Lake of the Woods control board. Click on the Basin Data link on the left hand side and you can get all kinds of info. Regards,http://www.lwcb.ca/
>to the top It would be intresting to know if the lake is up or down

O.K. I talked to a resort owner today and he said it is a little above normal (whatever that is) for this time of year. Plus, they had had 3 snow squalls go through before noon. People were coming in early with their supper, said they looked pretty chilly.
If you check the web site given above it also has a historical page that graphs the water level for every year. You can compare this year to your best year.
